# sample_type:          whole

<1> 'Uknı͒ˑ . 
<gloss> (Word of unknown meaning used in starting a myth)
<translation> Ukni .

<2> 'Ata háriva kunɂára̍ˑràhitihan̓ik .
<gloss> (Inferenital_particle) long they_were_dwelling .
<translation> They were living [there] .

<3> Xás 'uˑ̭mkun vaˑ̭ vúra kitc kunkupíttihanik pakunpakúrı̍ˑhva̍nàˑtìhàn̓ìk , pa'ávansas̓ , pakunpakúrı̍ˑhva̍nàˑtìhàn̓ìk , 'Ikriripanɂikmahátcra̕ᵅm .
<gloss> And they thus (predicative_particle) just they_used_to_do singing , the_men , singing , in_the_Amekyaram_sweathouse .
<translation> And they used to sing , the menfolks , used to sing in Amekyaram sweathouse .

<4> Xás vúra 'uˑ̭mkun hitíhaˑ̭n pakáˑ̯n kunívyiˑhmutihanik Peˑkxaréˑyav̓ , vaˑ̭ kumá'i'i pakunɂúˑhyananaˑtihan̓ik , hṹˑt 'ata pakunkupíttihe̕ᵉc , Yáˑsɂár̓a .
<gloss> And (predicative_particle) they all_the_time there went_in the_First_People , thus because they_were_talking_over , how (inferential_particle) they_will_do , Humans .
<translation> The Ikxareyavs went in there all the time , since they were talking over what Human was going to do .

<5> Tcavura pã́ˑnpay Pirickʸã́ˑrim káˑ̯n 'uθivkẽ́ˑva̍n'nìk , pakunɂúˑhyananaˑtihir̓ak , xás vúra 'uˑ̭m kunvı̃́ˑha pakáˑ̯n 'u'ȗˑm . 
<gloss> Then later Grizzly_Bear there went_in_with_them , where_they_were_talking_over , and (predicative_particle) him they_disliked when_there he_arrived .
<translation> Then later on Grizzly Bear went in there with them , when they were talking [it] over, and they did not like it when he arrived .

<6>  Xás kuníppẽ́̕ᵉr : " Nuˑ̭ tcimi núvyı̍ˑhcı̍prèˑv̓ìc , tcimi nu'ákkunavanve̕ᵉc . "
<gloss> Then they_told_him : " We (exhortative_particle) we_are_going_out , (exhortative_particle) we_are_going_hunting . "
<translation> Then they told him : " We are going out , we are going hunting . "

<7> Xás Pirickʸã́ˑrim 'uppı͒ˑp : " Naˑ̭ punavã́ˑra̍mèˑcàr̓à , naˑ̭ nípca̍ˑnne̍̕ᵉc . "
<gloss> Then Grizzly_Bear said : " I am_not_going , I I_will_keep_the_house . " 
<translation> Then Grizzly Bear said : " I am not going , I will keep the house. "

<8> Xás kunpı͒ˑp : " Tcṍˑr̓a . "
<gloss> Then they_said : " All right . "
<translation> Then they said : " All right . "

<9> Mã́ˑkka kitc 'uvṍˑnnı̍pàˑtì' maɂtı̃́ˑm̓itc . 
<gloss> Back onlz he_moved in_the_back_part_of_the_house .
<translation> He [Grizzly Bear] only moved back against the wall in the matimitc. 

<10> Xás kuníppẽ́̕ᵉr : " Tcímim̓an . " 
<gloss> Then they_told_him : " (Exhortative_particle)_indeed . "
<translation> Then they told him : " Do your own way . " 

<11> Xás mã́ˑmva̍nnìhìtc takunɂírunna̕ᵅ .
<gloss> Then a_little_up_slope they_traveled . 
<translation> Then they traveled up slope a little ways .

<12> Xás káˑ̯n xás kuntcúˑphina̕ᵅ , vaˑ̭ káˑ̯n 'ã́ˑpun kunivyíhicrihanik pakuntcúˑphinaˑtihan̓ik , kunpı͒ˑp : " Fã́ˑt kumá'i'i peˑkmahátcraˑm tanúpsa̍ˑmkìr̓ ? "
<gloss> Then there then they_talked , thus there on_the_ground they_sat_down talking , they_said : " What for in_the_sweathouse we_left_him ? "
<translation> And there they talked , and there they all sat down on the ground talking, they said : " What did we leave him there for in the sweathouse ? "

<13> Tcavura taxánanahicitc kóˑvúra kunparatánma̍ˑhpa̍nà̕ᵅ .
<gloss> Then after_a_while all they_turned_back .
<translation> Then after a while they all turned back ,

<14> Karixas kunpı͒ˑp : " Fã́ˑt kumá'i'i pávaˑ̭ káˑ̯n suɂ úkri̕ꜞ ? "
<gloss> Then they_said : " What for thus there inside he_is ? "
<translation> they said : " What is he in there for ? "

<15> Vúra takunɂȃy ˑ
<gloss> (Predicative_article) they_feared_him .
<translation> It was that they feared him .

<16> Táma vúra kunpavyíhuk kóˑvúr̓a , xás 'ikmahátcraˑ̭m kunpavyíhiv'raθ . 
<gloss> Then (predicative_particle) they_went_back all , then in_the_sweathouse they_went_back_in .
<translation> Then all got back down, and went back into the sweathouse .

<17> Kárixas 'ikmahátcraˑ̭m kunpavyíhic̓ .
<gloss> Then in_the_sweathouse they_sat_down .
<translation> Then all sat down in the sweathouse .

<18> Xás Pirickʸã́ˑrim 'uppı͒ˑp : " Hṹˑ takukúˑpha' ? "
<gloss> Then Grizzly_Bear said : How is_it_thus ? "
<translation> Then Grizzly Bear said : " What is the trouble ? "

<19> Xás yíθθa 'ı̃́ˑn kuníppẽ́̕ᵉr : " Tánùparatánma̍ˑhpà' . "
<gloss> Then one (subjective_particle) they_told_him : " We_turned_back ."
<translation> Then one of them told him: " We have turned back . "

<20> Xás yíθθ u'árihic̓ . 
<gloss> Then one started_to_sing .
<translation> Then one started to sing . 

<21> Xás kóˑvúr̓a kunpakúrı̍ˑ̭hvànà̕ᵅ , kuníppẽ́̕ᵉr : " 'Ṍˑk 'itcvánnihitc , tanúftcuy̓ . "
<gloss> Then all they_sang, they_told_him : " Hither a_little , we_are_crowded . "
<translation> Then all sang , they told him : " Come a little this way, we are crowded . "

<22> Mã́ˑkka kitc 'uváfnu̍ˑtcrìpàˑtì Pirickʸã́ˑr̓ìm . 
<gloss> Back onlY he_shrugged Grizzly_Bear . 
<translation> Grizzly Bear only shrugged back . 

<23> Xás kuníppẽ́̕ᵉr : " 'Iˑ̭mum vúra pu'ipvṍˑnnu̍pùkèˑcàrà ? "
<gloss> Then they_told_him : " You_(interrogative) (predicative_particle) you_will_not_go_out ? "
<translation> Then they told him : " Aren't you going to go out ? "

<24> " Pṹˑha̍r̓à , naˑ̭ vúra 'ṍˑk nikrẽ́ˑv̓ìc . "
<gloss> " No , I (predicative_particle) here I_shall_stay . "
<translation> " No , I'm going to stay here . "

<25> Xás yíθθ 'uppı͒ˑp : " Áθθiˑk tuvı̃́ˑc , tcími nuptáˑmmã́ˑxxi' . "
<gloss> Then one said : " Cold it_is_already , (exhortative_particle) let's_scrape_up_the_coals . "
<translation> Then one said: " It is getting cold, let's scrape up the coals . "

<26> Xás 'áhup kuníyu̍ˑnkìr̓ , 'ikmahatcram'áhup . 
<gloss> Then wood they_put_on_the_fire, sweathouse_wood .
<translation> Then they put wood on the fire , sweathouse-wood .

<27> Tcavura pã́ˑnpay 'imfíˑ̯r tuvı̃́ˑc .
<gloss> Then later hot it_got .
<translation> Then after a while it got hot .

<28> Súɂ kunɂíxxuprim'va . 
<gloss> Down they_prostrated_themselves .
<translation> They all got down face on the floor .

<29> 'Uˑ̭m vúra kitc 'àɂ úkriˑ̭ maɂtı̃́ˑmitc Pirickʸã́ˑr̓im , puxayvúrakẽ́ˑna̍tìhàr̓à . 
<gloss> He (predicative_particle) only up he_sat in_the_back_of_the_house Grizzly_Bear, he_did_not_move . "
<translation> Grizzly Bear alone was sitting up in the matimitc , he never moved .

<30> Tcavura kóˑvúr̓a kunpakúrı̍ˑ̭hvànà̕ˑ̭ kúkku̕ᵘm .
<gloss> Then all they_sang again .
<translation> Then they were all singing again .

<31> Vúra 'uˑ̭m puxxʷítc 'imfíˑ̯r tuvı̃́ˑc . 
<gloss> (Predicative_particle) it very hot it_got .
<translation> Then it got awfully hot .

<32> Vaˑ̭ vúra kunímmʸu̍ˑ̭stì Pirickʸã́ˑr̓im .
<gloss> Thus (predicative_particle) they_were_looking_at_him Grizzly_Bear .
<translation> They kept looking at Grizzly Bear .

<33> Tcavura tapã́ˑnpay pamúttiˑ̭v kúnic tattṹˑppìt̓càs , toˑmxurukúvraˑn pamútti̕ꜞv , toˑmtaránku̕ᵘ .
<gloss> Then later his_ears like already_small_ones , they_melted_down his_ears, he_was_sweltering . 
<translation> Then after a while his ears seemed to be small , his ears melted down , he was sweltering .

<34> Tcavura taxánnahictitc tcímaxmáy 'ù'àˑ̭ssìc pata̍príhak̓ , vúra tóˑmtcax , tapukunickẽ́ˑnnatihar̓a .
<gloss> Then after_a_while all_at_once he_lay_down on_the_pavement , (predicative_particle) he_was_hot , he_could_hardly_move .
<translation> Then after a while all at once he lay down on the pavement, it was like he couldn't move .

<35> 'Uma vúra vaˑ̭ kunpakúrı̍ˑhvànàˑtì 'imfirayã́̕ᵅk .
<gloss> Just (predicative_particle) thus they_were_singing in_the_heat .
<translation> Just the same they kept on singing in the heat .

<36> Vúra pukúnicxútihap hṹ̕ᵘt , takunɂáˑpùn'mà tóˑmkúhir̓uv .
<gloss> (Predicative_particle) it_was_like_they_did_not_heed how , they_knew he_was_getting_sweltered .
<translation> They paid no attention to him , they knew that he was getting sweltered .

<37> Tapu'imtaranã́ˑmhı̍tìhàrà pamútti̕ꜞv poˑpvṍˑnsip . 
<gloss> They_were_invisible his_ears when_he_got_up_again . 
<translation> His ears were invisible when he got up again .

<38> Vúra tattṹˑppìtcàs pamútti̕ꜞv , toˑmxurukúvraˑ̭n peˑmfíra̍mmṹ̕ᵘk . 
<gloss> (predicative_article) they_were_already_little_ones his_ears , they_were_melted with_the_heat .
<translation> They were little , his ears , they were melted with the heat .

<39> Kárixas 'úkvu̍ˑ̭nnu̍pùkàn̓ìk . 
<gloss> Then he_staggered_out .
<translation> Then he staggered out .

<40> Kárixas 'úppa̍ˑn'nìk , poˑpíttìθu̍nàn̓ìk : " Xáy faˑ̭t 'ík vúra vaˑ̭ naˑ̭ niθíttı̍ˑmti' pamikʸunpákkur̓i ; naˑ̭ púvaˑˑ̭ nanívaˑ̭hara pamikʸunpákkur̓iˑ " .
<gloss> Then he_said , when_he_looked_back : " May not_more indeed (predicative_particle) thus I I_hear your_song ; me not_thus is_for_me your_song . "  
<translation> Then he said looking back: " I must never hear your song any more ; your song will not do for me . "

<41> Pirickʸã́ˑrim vaˑ̭ 'úpa̍ˑn'nìk : " Xáy faˑ̭t 'ík vúra vaˑ̭ naˑ̭ niθíttı̍ˑmtì pamikʸunpákkur̓i . Naˑ̭ tánì'a̍hù̕ᵘ . " 
<gloss> Grizzly_Bear thus he_said : " May not_more indeed (predicative_particle) thus I I_hear your_song . I I_am_already_traveling . "
<translation> Grizzly Bear said it : " I must never hear your song any more . I am going to travel . "

<42> Xás 'úkfu̍ˑkrã̍ˑnìk 'ikkʸurã́̕ᵅk .
<gloss> Then he_climbed the_ridge .
<translation> Then he climbed up slope .

<43> 'Uˑ̭m vúra kunxússe̍ˑntìhànìk kiri húˑk u'ȗˑm , vúra kunvı̃́ˑhan̓ik . 
<gloss> He (predicative_particle) they_had_been_thinking may somewhere he_go_to , (predicative_article) they_disliked_him .
<translation> They had been wishing for him to go off , for they disliked him .

<44> Xás 'uˑ̭m vúra vaˑ̭ póˑkfu̍ˑkrã̍·̬nìk pirickʸã́ˑrim 'upárìhı̍crìhàn̓ìk .
<gloss> Then he (predicative_particle) thus when_he_climbed grizzly_bear he_was_transformed_into .
<translation> And when he climbed up slope he was metamorphosed into the grizzly bear .

<45> Víri payváhiˑ̭m vúra kári vár uvı̃́ˑhiti 'Ikriripanpákkur̓i . 
<gloss> And now (predicative_particle) at_this_time still he_dislikes Amekyaram_Sweathouse_songs .
<translation> He still dislikes those songs now .

<46> Pa'áraˑ̭r tupakurı̃́ˑhva̍hàˑk 'Ikriripanpákkuri márukninay vaˑ̭ xás vúr óˑkviˑpti' , páyváhiˑm vòˑkùpìttì' . 
<gloss> When_a_person sings Amekyaram_Sweathouse_songs up_slope_anywhere thus then (predicative_particle) he_runs_away, now he_does_it . 
<translation> Whenever a person sings Amekyaram sweathouse songs in mountain places anywhere , he runs away , he does so now .

<47> Kári vari vúra voˑ'áˑ̯yti papákkur̓i . 
<gloss> At_this_time still (predicative_particle) he_fears those_songs .
<translation> He still fears those songs .

<48> Vaˑ̭ vúra páyváhiˑ̭m 'úθvuˑyti pirickʸãˑrimɂáhàssu̍r̓àr , Peˑkríripanpákkur̓i . 
<gloss> Thus (predicative_particle) now it_is_called grizzly_bear_driver-away , those_Amekyaram_Sweathouse_songs .
<translation> It is still called grizzly-bear drive-away-medicine , those Amekyaram sweathouse songs .

